OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNorth East
OL,4,
OL,5,CWednesday:FA bright start with a few
OL,6,Fscattered showers, before a band of
OL,7,Frain spreads northeastwards across all
OL,8,Fparts during the afternoon. Turning
OL,9,Fmore showery by the evening.
OL,10,FTemperatures near normal.
OL,11,
OL,12,COutlook for Thursday to Saturday:
OL,13,FBreezy on Thursday, with sunny spells
OL,14,Fand showers, heavy and thundery. Fewer
OL,15,Fshowers likely on Friday. Drier on
OL,16,FSaturday, but still the chance of a
OL,17,Ffew showers. Staying cool.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
